WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:24.816 --> 00:25.817
[ROARS]

00:31.406 --> 00:32.824
[ROARS]

00:40.749 --> 00:42.250
[ROARS]

00:47.922 --> 00:49.299
Lower the prisoner.

00:49.382 --> 00:50.592
[METAL CLANGING]

00:53.428 --> 00:54.262
[JIM GRUNTS]

00:54.345 --> 00:58.600
Are you still refusing to admit
your friends had any hand in this?

00:58.683 --> 01:03.438
It's my fault. I'm responsible.
Everything they did was for me.

01:03.521 --> 01:09.778
Then this is beyond even my authority.
I am sorry.

01:09.861 --> 01:12.906
James Lake, Jr., you stand accused

01:12.989 --> 01:17.660
of unleashing Gunmar on the world
and failing to protect trollkind.

01:17.744 --> 01:19.954
If you let me out, I can fight.

01:20.038 --> 01:23.958
You will face trial
in front of the Tribunal for your crime.

01:24.042 --> 01:26.544
If found guilty, as you say you are...

01:26.628 --> 01:30.256
The consequence could be... death.

01:30.340 --> 01:33.051
But an offer of mercy is on the table.

01:33.134 --> 01:37.055
If you surrender the Amulet
to be destroyed, you will be exiled.

01:37.138 --> 01:38.973
And your life spared.

01:39.057 --> 01:42.060
I don't understand.
Then there won't be a Trollhunter.

01:42.143 --> 01:44.103
For too long, we trolls have relied

01:44.187 --> 01:47.440
on Merlin's antiquated magics
to shelter us.

01:47.524 --> 01:52.529
As for the evil we face tomorrow,
that is up for our own race to decide,

01:52.612 --> 01:54.739
not some human child.

01:56.950 --> 02:03.873
I'm aware this is a terrible choice, young
one, but it is solely yours to make.

02:03.957 --> 02:08.627
The trial begins at dawn.
You have until then to decide.

02:11.756 --> 02:13.007
[GRUNTS]

02:19.055 --> 02:20.932
[BOTH SNORING]

02:22.642 --> 02:25.103
[SNORES]

02:25.687 --> 02:27.522
[JIM] Is this what you wanted?

02:28.773 --> 02:30.191
To hurt everyone?

02:31.442 --> 02:33.361
To ruin my life?

02:34.320 --> 02:36.239
Why did you choose me, huh?

02:38.533 --> 02:41.828
I wish I never picked you up
in the first place.

02:44.414 --> 02:45.748
[CLANKS]

02:46.332 --> 02:48.167
You made a mistake.

02:50.587 --> 02:51.754
[SIGHS]

03:02.599 --> 03:07.312
[JIM] You made a mistake.
I wish I never picked you up.

03:12.483 --> 03:17.447
[UNKAR] So the Amulet made a mistake,
eh? You would not be the first.

03:18.072 --> 03:21.284
- Who are you?
- You don't recognize me?

03:21.367 --> 03:26.372
Perhaps a hint or two. I didn't have
much luck being a Trollhunter, either.

03:26.956 --> 03:33.922
Trained by Blinky? Couldn't last a day?
Ripped limb from limb?

03:34.005 --> 03:36.841
Whoa. Unkar the Unfortunate?

03:36.925 --> 03:42.180
That's what stuck?
I was hoping for "Unkar the Ultimate."

03:42.263 --> 03:43.932
Why are you here?

03:44.015 --> 03:48.728
You wish you never picked up
the Amulet in the first place?

03:48.811 --> 03:53.816
Well, I'm here to offer you
what I never had,

03:53.900 --> 03:56.027
a second chance.

03:58.571 --> 03:59.572
[TICKING]

04:02.200 --> 04:03.201
[ALARM BLARING]

04:03.284 --> 04:05.203
[MAN ON RADIO] Good morning,
Arcadia Oaks!

04:05.286 --> 04:08.998
If you're still in bed, you are missing
the most beautiful sunrise.

04:09.582 --> 04:15.338
[GASPS] This should not be happening.
I'm in a cage. But where is the cage?

04:20.093 --> 04:21.094
[GASPS]

04:23.596 --> 04:24.597
[SNORES]

04:28.101 --> 04:30.395
What is going on right now?

04:33.481 --> 04:35.525
[SIGHS] Not raccoons.

04:36.192 --> 04:38.861
We're late for school, Jimbo. No lunch?

04:38.945 --> 04:40.405
No. What?

04:40.488 --> 04:43.241
You said you were making
something special for me this morning.

04:43.324 --> 04:45.368
Nah. Maybe it's for the best.
I am on a diet.

04:45.451 --> 04:48.746
You've been on a diet
for 14 years, Tobes.

04:48.830 --> 04:51.291
Long-term goals. My
body's still changing.

04:51.916 --> 04:55.461
So you don't know that
I'm a Trollhunter?

04:56.421 --> 04:59.841
Okay. You really gotta stop
skipping breakfast, Jimbo.

04:59.924 --> 05:03.594
It's the most important meal of the day.
Come on, we're gonna be late for school!

05:03.678 --> 05:05.430
Let's take the canals.

05:05.513 --> 05:06.514
The canals.

05:07.432 --> 05:08.433
The Amulet.

05:09.350 --> 05:12.478
A second chance! [LAUGHS]

05:13.062 --> 05:16.566
Tobes, go the long way!
I don't wanna take the canals today.

05:16.983 --> 05:17.900
Your call!

05:18.943 --> 05:20.987
[BOTH GRUNTING]

05:21.070 --> 05:21.946
[BELL RINGING]

05:22.030 --> 05:24.657
Final bell! We're so late,
our kids are gonna have detention!

05:30.288 --> 05:31.331
[GASPS]

05:31.414 --> 05:34.167
- Did you say something?
- Uh... Nope.

05:38.087 --> 05:41.591
The Peloponnesian War
was actually three wars

05:41.674 --> 05:43.676
fought between Athens and Sparta.

05:43.760 --> 05:46.888
The first war is known
as the Archimedean War.

05:46.971 --> 05:49.682
- Type that into your search engines.
- I can't believe it.

05:49.766 --> 05:52.769
Everything's the same...
but not the same.

05:52.852 --> 05:55.521
What's going on with you, dude?
You've been acting weird all morning.

05:55.605 --> 05:59.484
I don't even know how to explain, Tobes.
Let's meet up with Claire and talk.

05:59.567 --> 06:00.610
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

06:00.693 --> 06:02.070
Claire? Like "secret crush" Claire?

06:02.153 --> 06:04.781
You taking crazy pills?
She barely knows you exist.

06:04.864 --> 06:06.157
Oh, yeah, right.

06:06.240 --> 06:11.370
- Jim, would you agree with Herodotus...?
- Strickler! I mean, uh, uh...

06:11.454 --> 06:13.748
- Yes, yes. [STAMMERS] Absolutely.
- [BELL RINGING]

06:13.831 --> 06:15.166
[LAUGHING]

06:15.249 --> 06:17.043
- Jim, may I have a word?
- [GASPS]

06:17.794 --> 06:19.378
Jim, you seem distracted.

06:19.462 --> 06:22.590
I believe I'm overdue
for a conversation with your mother.

06:22.673 --> 06:26.177
No! No, no, no, no.
Stay away from my mom!

06:27.345 --> 06:28.638
[SNIFFS]

06:28.721 --> 06:29.597
Oh...

06:30.056 --> 06:33.309
I want all of you
to be made of iron. Iron!

06:33.392 --> 06:35.311
Oh, you have got to be kidding me!

06:35.394 --> 06:37.772
I don't know what I
feel more sorry for...

06:37.855 --> 06:39.023
- you or the rope!
- [EXHALES]

06:39.107 --> 06:41.609
- [LAUGHS]
- Claire! Claire, we need to talk!

06:41.692 --> 06:44.320
Um, what? Sorry, have we met?

06:44.403 --> 06:47.990
Oh, right. You don't know who I am.
I mean, you do, but...

06:48.074 --> 06:50.243
[STAMMERS] I mean, you will! [CHUCKLES]

06:50.993 --> 06:53.329
- Yeesh! Come on, Claire.
- Wait!

06:53.412 --> 06:57.583
Your brother's named Enrique,
but, pretty soon, he'll be NotEnrique.

06:57.667 --> 07:02.171
- What are you talking about?
- Sorry, we were just going away from you.

07:02.255 --> 07:05.550
So, bye, whatever your name is. Ugh.

07:05.633 --> 07:08.761
But Shakespeare!
You're Juliet and I'm Rome...

07:10.930 --> 07:12.140
[SIGHS]

07:12.223 --> 07:16.519
Tobes, I'm telling you,
in my other life, she's my girlfriend.

07:16.602 --> 07:20.481
Man, you dream big.
Even in my imagination, I'm only a duke.

07:20.565 --> 07:22.567
Uh... It's not my imagination.

07:22.650 --> 07:26.446
Tell me about the creatures
and maybe I'll let you out.

07:26.529 --> 07:28.322
Okay, nothing to see here.

07:28.406 --> 07:32.743
Okay, wait. Last time,
I intervened and Steve fights me.

07:32.827 --> 07:35.163
Better Eli than you. That kid's
performing a public service.

07:35.246 --> 07:41.085
You were telling me about the monsters
you saw this morning with fangs.

07:41.169 --> 07:43.921
- And what was it again?
- [ELI] Stone for skin. In the canal.

07:44.505 --> 07:47.675
If I do nothing,
Steve won't be on my case.

07:47.758 --> 07:50.261
I won't have to worry about him anymore.
Or maybe...

07:50.344 --> 07:53.431
Dude, you've been
a real braincase all morning.

07:53.514 --> 07:55.600
What did you just call me, buttsnack?

07:56.184 --> 07:59.145
- Uh, uh... Nothing? Jim? Jim?
- [GRUNTS]

08:01.814 --> 08:02.857
[TOBY] Ow!

08:02.940 --> 08:07.945
[GASPS] Distract me from the pain.
Tell me again. I have a Warhammer?

08:08.029 --> 08:09.447
And you're a duke.

08:09.530 --> 08:12.325
Ha! And I thought I had
a big imagination.

08:12.408 --> 08:15.161
Look, Jimbo, we're nobodies,
but that's okay.

08:15.244 --> 08:17.038
It's not imagin... [GASPS]

08:18.581 --> 08:22.001
Yes! I can prove it! Tobes.
Tobes, come here.

08:23.211 --> 08:24.504
[GRUNTS]

08:25.379 --> 08:29.175
- Where'd it go? [SIGHS]
- You wanted to show me a pile of rocks.

08:29.258 --> 08:32.220
No, Tobes, the Amulet.
It was right here.

08:32.303 --> 08:34.388
[SIGHS] Maybe someone else was chosen.

08:34.472 --> 08:37.058
Well, Jim, this has been memorable.

08:37.140 --> 08:40.477
And since somebody forgot my lunch
today, I'm going home to eat.

08:40.561 --> 08:42.438
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- [SIGHS]

08:43.981 --> 08:44.982
[SIGHS]

08:47.443 --> 08:52.281
It's a mundane life,
but at least you are alive, eh?

08:52.365 --> 08:56.202
- You could've helped me out.
- Oh, they can't hear me. Only you can.

08:56.285 --> 08:57.995
Besides, what would I have said?

08:58.079 --> 09:01.582
Talking ball of light says,
"Listen to the boy.

09:01.666 --> 09:04.460
He once possessed a magic Amulet"?

09:04.544 --> 09:07.588
But then who has the Amulet now?

09:07.672 --> 09:11.050
Oh, that is the Trollhunter's concern.

09:11.133 --> 09:16.556
Remember, you are just Jim Lake, Jr.
You're getting a second chance.

09:16.639 --> 09:20.560
Enjoy it. It may surprise you.

09:20.643 --> 09:22.144
[ALARM BLARING]

09:22.228 --> 09:23.229
[SIGHS]

09:23.312 --> 09:25.523
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

09:25.606 --> 09:28.109
Muy bien, Mr. Lake. A-plus.

09:28.192 --> 09:30.319
Spectacular!

09:30.403 --> 09:33.197
Wake up! Don't want to sleep
through your big day!

09:33.281 --> 09:37.243
- Mom's special birthday pancakes!
- [CHUCKLES]

09:37.326 --> 09:39.328
[INAUDIBLE]

09:51.424 --> 09:53.175
- [GIGGLES]
- [CHUCKLES]

09:57.763 --> 10:00.433
I will kiss thy lips.

10:04.270 --> 10:05.563
Ha!

10:08.024 --> 10:09.775
[INHALES, EXHALES]

10:10.943 --> 10:14.238
[DRAAL] If my destiny is
to not hold the sword...

10:15.281 --> 10:19.035
perhaps it is to teach you
how to properly wield it.

10:20.745 --> 10:22.580
Mimic my movements, Trollhunter.

10:24.415 --> 10:26.125
[GRUNTING]

10:28.210 --> 10:30.171
[GRUNTS]

10:33.883 --> 10:35.968
[SIGHS]

10:53.653 --> 10:56.781
- [EXHALES]
- [BELL TOLLING]

11:02.453 --> 11:03.537
[GASPS]

11:05.581 --> 11:07.500
Killahead Bridge.

11:09.001 --> 11:12.004
[STRICKLER]
You're sure he hasn't told anyone?

11:12.421 --> 11:14.924
[NOMURA] Trust me, I know him.

11:15.007 --> 11:18.344
He's stubborn. He works alone.

11:18.427 --> 11:21.680
Good. Then all we do is lay the bait

11:21.764 --> 11:25.476
- and Gunmar will be free.
- [GASPS]

11:26.060 --> 11:27.686
Oh, no. Gunmar.

11:31.816 --> 11:33.150
[GRUNTS]

11:37.238 --> 11:40.449
Perhaps you should consider
reading my books instead of eating them.

11:41.033 --> 11:42.868
- [JIM] Blinky!
- Hm? [YELLS]

11:44.495 --> 11:47.623
- Hmm.
- A human! Be gone, fleshbag!

11:47.706 --> 11:51.585
Or... Or else my sizable friend
here will eat you!

11:52.420 --> 11:54.922
- Aaarrrgghh!!!'s a pacifist.
- Pacifist.

11:55.005 --> 11:57.299
How did you know that?

11:57.383 --> 12:01.011
Unkar sent me back in time
to give me a second chance.

12:01.095 --> 12:03.305
Unkar? [LAUGHS] That's impossible!

12:03.389 --> 12:07.643
No troll, even a spirit,
holds the power to change fate itself!

12:07.726 --> 12:11.772
Fate changed, okay?
And now I need to find the Trollhunter.

12:11.856 --> 12:14.150
They're building Killahead Bridge!

12:14.233 --> 12:15.776
Killahead?

12:15.860 --> 12:20.114
Um, actually, we believe
you, young human.

12:20.197 --> 12:21.740
[GROANS] Finally. Thank you.

12:21.824 --> 12:24.493
Aaarrrgghh!!!, go find
the Trollhunter, Draal.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.662
Draal is the Trollhunter?

12:26.745 --> 12:30.166
- And have him bring... a gaggletack.
- [GASPS]

12:30.249 --> 12:32.209
- You think I'm a changeling?
- Quick, restrain him!

12:33.794 --> 12:37.173
- He's escaping! Quick!
- [AAARRRGGHH!!!] He's got moves.

12:37.256 --> 12:41.010
Indeed. Clearly, his evil masters
have trained him well.

12:41.594 --> 12:43.804
[GRUNTS]

12:43.888 --> 12:47.600
Why can't I find anyone
who believes me? Strickler!

12:47.683 --> 12:53.355
Goodbye, Arcadia Oaks High.
Consider this my resignation.

12:55.691 --> 12:56.942
Strickler, we need to talk!

12:57.026 --> 13:00.321
Jim! These aren't my
normal office hours.

13:00.404 --> 13:05.451
- I believe you mean "Mr." Strickler.
- I know, Strickler. I know your secret.

13:05.534 --> 13:06.619
I know everything.

13:06.702 --> 13:11.332
[CHUCKLES]
And what would "everything" entail?

13:11.415 --> 13:13.375
The Killahead Bridge.

13:13.459 --> 13:14.543
Killa-what?

13:14.627 --> 13:18.047
- [CLEARS THROAT]
- I know you're a changeling.

13:18.130 --> 13:20.299
What? [SNARLS]

13:21.967 --> 13:24.595
[BOTH GRUNTING]

13:24.678 --> 13:26.764
I know you want to release Gunmar

13:26.847 --> 13:30.059
so changelings will gain
the respect they deserve,

13:30.142 --> 13:31.227
but you're wrong.

13:31.310 --> 13:33.187
It doesn't happen that way.

13:34.230 --> 13:36.315
You'll always be an impure to him.

13:36.398 --> 13:37.733
[BOTH GRUNTING]

13:40.736 --> 13:42.154
How did you...?

13:43.822 --> 13:47.535
- How do you know all this?
- I know it because I was the Trollhunter.

13:47.618 --> 13:48.452
[GASPS]

13:48.536 --> 13:50.913
I've lived this,
but I messed everything up.

13:50.996 --> 13:54.708
And now, I'm stuck in the past,
and believe it or not,

13:54.792 --> 14:00.464
you and I work together to put an end
to Gunmar once and for all.

14:02.550 --> 14:04.468
[GRUNTS]

14:06.554 --> 14:08.180
[PANTS]

14:09.473 --> 14:10.933
[GASPS]

14:12.059 --> 14:16.855
A human Trollhunter?
This would change everything.

14:16.939 --> 14:20.568
But why on earth would I ally
with a Trollhun...?

14:20.651 --> 14:22.570
[ELECTRICITY BUZZES]

14:23.153 --> 14:24.864
- You believe me, then. [GRUNTS]
- [EXPLOSION]

14:27.908 --> 14:32.037
It doesn't matter now.
I fear it's too late.

14:32.121 --> 14:35.124
The invasion has begun.

14:35.207 --> 14:36.959
We need to get to the museum.

14:39.920 --> 14:41.964
[ALARMS BLARING]

14:42.047 --> 14:46.176
Why do you want to go to the museum?
There's nothing but death there.

14:46.260 --> 14:47.469
That's where the Amulet is.

14:47.553 --> 14:50.431
- If it started this, it can undo this.
- [PHONE RING TONE] I am Gun Robot.

14:50.514 --> 14:52.933
- Tobes!
- It's true! Everything you said is true!

14:53.017 --> 14:54.894
- What the heck is going on?
- Die!

14:54.977 --> 14:56.854
- Ay-yi-yi! [GRUNTS]
- [LAUGHS]

14:56.937 --> 14:59.189
- [JIM] Find Claire, get somewhere safe.
- Claire?

14:59.273 --> 15:01.108
[GLADYS] Come here!
Now for the main course!

15:01.191 --> 15:02.568
Tobes! Toby!

15:03.527 --> 15:05.654
[RADIO ANNOUNCER] <span style= "style_1"
/>I repeat, this is not a prank.

15:05.738 --> 15:08.949
There have been strange
animal attacks all over town.

15:10.242 --> 15:11.952
People are advised to stay indoor...

15:13.954 --> 15:16.999
Oh, no. Donny! Shut
the... They're coming!

15:17.458 --> 15:19.668
- [CLATTERING]
- [MAN ON RADIO SCREAMING]

15:19.752 --> 15:21.253
Let's get to that museum.

15:21.337 --> 15:23.547
[ENGINE REVVING]

15:24.256 --> 15:26.133
- [SIREN WAILING]
- [GRUNTS]

15:32.348 --> 15:35.559
So, if you are from another future,
what happens to me?

15:36.143 --> 15:37.686
[SIGHS] Mom!

15:38.354 --> 15:41.148
I'm eaten, aren't I?
By that savage brute, Bular!

15:41.231 --> 15:43.108
- [PHONE RINGS]
- Mom!

15:43.192 --> 15:46.320
- Jim! Where are you?
- Mom, I'm okay! I'm with Mr. Strickler.

15:46.403 --> 15:49.990
[BARBARA] I don't know what's going on.
I'm coming to you. Tell me where you...

15:50.074 --> 15:52.660
Mom, you need to get somewhere safe.
Lock the wards.

15:52.743 --> 15:53.994
[MAN ON RADIO] Stay inside.

15:54.078 --> 15:56.372
- [GRUNTS]
- [TIRES SCREECH]

15:57.289 --> 15:58.499
[BARBARA] Listen...

15:58.582 --> 16:01.210
- I need you to be safe.
- [MAN ON RADIO] Code Black.

16:01.293 --> 16:04.463
- Initiating lockdown.
- Honey, I love you.

16:04.546 --> 16:06.256
- I love you too.
- [EXPLODING]

16:06.340 --> 16:08.133
- [GASPS] Mom? Mom!
- [DIAL TONE SOUNDING]

16:08.217 --> 16:10.719
They've hit the cell towers.
We're almost there.

16:13.514 --> 16:15.432
[TIRES SCREECH]

16:17.768 --> 16:19.520
- [GRUNTS]
- [GASPS]

16:19.603 --> 16:22.147
[TIRES SCREECH]

16:25.901 --> 16:27.194
Impure.

16:27.277 --> 16:28.445
[GASPS]

16:28.529 --> 16:30.114
Get outta here! Get outta here!

16:30.197 --> 16:32.992
You'd better be right, Trollhunter.
There's no...

16:33.075 --> 16:34.326
[SCREAMS]

16:37.079 --> 16:39.915
[JIM COUGHS, GRUNTS]

16:43.919 --> 16:44.837
Gunmar.

16:45.421 --> 16:50.884
After all you've done, Stricklander,
you would flee in our hour of triumph?

16:50.968 --> 16:54.638
Gunmar, Your Dark Excellence.
You are out.

16:55.180 --> 17:00.519
I so wanted to be there,
but... uh, I had papers to grade.

17:00.602 --> 17:02.187
- [GROWLS]
- Bular...

17:03.897 --> 17:05.898
So, that's how it is.

17:06.983 --> 17:10.029
Go. Get out of here.
They want me, not you.

17:10.945 --> 17:12.656
I can help you fight them.

17:12.740 --> 17:13.949
It's too late.

17:16.617 --> 17:18.287
Get to the museum!

17:18.369 --> 17:20.039
[BOTH GROWLING]

17:20.122 --> 17:21.623
[GRUNTING]

17:25.085 --> 17:26.920
[PANTS]

17:30.299 --> 17:33.302
[STEVE] Palchuk! Palchuk! Palchuk!

17:33.385 --> 17:36.096
Come at me, mouth-breathers!
Palchuk never dies.

17:36.180 --> 17:37.473
Palchuk never...

17:38.057 --> 17:41.435
Oh, yeah? You want a piece of this, too?
[WHOOPING]

17:44.521 --> 17:46.023
[GRUNTS]

17:46.607 --> 17:51.403
Come along. We're missing all the fun.
[CHUCKLES]

17:51.487 --> 17:53.906
[ROARING AND GRUNTING]

17:58.952 --> 17:59.787
Okay.

18:10.798 --> 18:12.633
[GASPS] Draal.

18:12.716 --> 18:13.926
Oh, no.

18:17.179 --> 18:18.639
[SIGHS]

18:19.765 --> 18:20.766
[SIGHS]

18:23.310 --> 18:24.311
Sorry.

18:25.145 --> 18:25.979
[GASPS]

18:26.063 --> 18:27.022
The Amulet.

18:27.106 --> 18:30.150
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

18:30.734 --> 18:31.819
[GASPS]

18:32.903 --> 18:35.739
No! No, no, no, no!

18:35.823 --> 18:38.742
For the glory of Merlin,
Daylight is mine to command.

18:38.826 --> 18:41.495
For the glory of Merlin,
Daylight is mine to command.

18:41.578 --> 18:43.872
For the glory of Merlin,
Daylight is mine to command.

18:43.956 --> 18:47.876
Come on! For the glory of Merlin,
Daylight is mine to command.

18:47.960 --> 18:50.504
Please work! Please work!

18:50.587 --> 18:53.048
For the glory of Merlin. Please!

18:53.132 --> 18:55.968
For the glory of Merlin,
Daylight is mine to command!

18:56.343 --> 18:59.513
[RUMBLING]

18:59.596 --> 19:01.014
Please.

19:02.391 --> 19:03.392
Please.

19:04.601 --> 19:05.769
Please!

19:06.937 --> 19:09.439
Please! Unkar! Anyone!

19:09.857 --> 19:13.235
I can't do this alone!

19:14.987 --> 19:16.405
[SOBBING] Please.

19:19.449 --> 19:23.453
I'm the Trollhunter! [PANTING]

19:24.329 --> 19:25.330
[GRUNTS]

19:30.127 --> 19:31.587
[SIGHS]

19:31.670 --> 19:34.256
[SIGHS] I'm the Trollhunter.

19:35.048 --> 19:38.260
I am the Trollhunter.
I know I'm the Trollhunter.

19:39.887 --> 19:42.097
[GRUNTS]

19:44.433 --> 19:45.684
I'm the Trollhunter...

19:46.977 --> 19:48.729
Amulet or not.

19:54.693 --> 19:58.530
[UNKAR]
If you walk out that door, you will die.

19:58.614 --> 19:59.990
What choice do I have?

20:00.073 --> 20:05.787
Oh, there's always a choice.
Run away, save your skin.

20:05.871 --> 20:07.372
That's not who I am.

20:08.081 --> 20:13.962
Out there, they need a Trollhunter,
and a Trollhunter fights till the end.

20:16.715 --> 20:23.180
[MERLIN] Ah, now you're getting it.
My Amulet does not make mistakes.

20:23.764 --> 20:25.057
Your Amulet?

20:25.766 --> 20:26.808
[GASPS]

20:27.392 --> 20:28.393
Merlin?

20:29.102 --> 20:33.732
You know, it is customary
to kneel before a wizard.

20:36.985 --> 20:38.528
You did this.

20:38.612 --> 20:40.197
Gunmar is free,

20:40.280 --> 20:42.616
Trollmarket is in peril,

20:42.699 --> 20:45.452
and of all creatures in our worlds,

20:45.535 --> 20:48.497
I chose you.

20:51.875 --> 20:54.753
Now, show them why.

21:02.636 --> 21:04.096
[GROWLS]

21:06.598 --> 21:08.475
[GRUNTS]

21:09.518 --> 21:11.311
[TICKS, CLICKS]

21:11.395 --> 21:13.397
[GRUNTS]

21:13.814 --> 21:14.856
[GASPS]

21:18.568 --> 21:21.280
[CLEARS THROAT]
Master Jim, is everything all right?

21:22.489 --> 21:24.574
[PANTS]

21:25.492 --> 21:29.538
- Are you okay? Did they rough you up?
- No, Claire, I'm... I'm okay!

21:29.621 --> 21:32.165
We've come to escort you
to the Tribunal.

21:32.249 --> 21:35.502
They say if you're found guilty,
you could die. Is that true?

21:35.585 --> 21:38.505
He would walk free
if he surrenders the Amulet.

21:38.588 --> 21:41.008
What is your choice, Trollhunter?

21:41.091 --> 21:43.093
Uh, the one where he doesn't die?

21:43.176 --> 21:46.847
No. I'm keeping my Amulet.

21:46.930 --> 21:49.349
Are you serious? That's what you want?

21:49.433 --> 21:52.644
Yeah, Tobes. Never been more sure.

21:54.271 --> 21:56.189
I'll face whatever comes my way.

21:56.273 --> 21:57.524
- [GASPS]
- Jim...

21:57.607 --> 21:59.359
So be it, Trollhunter.

21:59.443 --> 22:01.153
Your trial awaits.

22:06.992 --> 22:10.078
- [SNIFFLES]
- [GROANS]

